parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to lock or become difficult to turn, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or difficult to turn
the steering wheel locks in place
a clunking or grinding noise is heard during turns
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
the power steering pump reservoir is full but the system is not functioning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column or shaft can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock in place, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: A clunking or grinding noise is heard during turns
the steering wheel feels stiff or difficult to turn
the steering wheel vibrates or shakes
a popping or cracking noise is heard from the steering column.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transfer case clutch plates can cause the all-wheel drive system to malfunction, leading to loss of traction and potential accidents.
symptoms: The all-wheel drive light is illuminated
the vehicle lacks traction or slips during acceleration
the transfer case clutch plates are worn or damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel system failures, including fuel tank pressure sensor malfunctions and fuel pump failures, can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to potential accidents or fires.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start properly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sway bar link can cause the vehicle to swerve or lose control, increasing the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Problems with the front suspension and steering can cause vibrations, noise, and instability, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective paint job and windshield can cause cosmetic issues and compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, potentially leading to safety issues.
